Parts list for Destiny 2 Ghost Eye

TFT display with integrated ESP32 - https://www.waveshare.com/esp32-s3-lcd-1.28.htm
  No need for the toudh one unless you plan on poking your ghost in the eye a bunch.

90° USB C cable - https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0FPLYB6QN 
  I still had to grind off a bit of the plastic on the back of it to make it fit well. Avoid metal ones. 

A 2 wire battery with a JST 1.25 connector on it. 
  I used a 603450 1800mAh one. 

A small latching switch so you can leave the battery plugged in and still turn it off. 

Eight 6x2mm neodymium magnets
